-> JWT (json web token) explained

JWT (JSON Web Token) hi wo "main technology" hai jiske andar ye Access aur Refresh tokens aate hain.

Samajh le ki JWT ek Digital Identity Card hai, aur Access/Refresh us card ke alag-alag versions hain. 🎫✨

JWT Kya Hai? (The Big Picture)
JWT ek open standard hai (RFC 7519) jo do parties (client aur server) ke beech mein information ko ek secure JSON object ke roop mein bhejta hai. Ye information verified aur trusted hoti hai kyunki is par server ke digital signature hote hain.

Access Token vs Refresh Token (Deep Dive) 🌊
1. Access Token (The Temporary Pass) ⏱️
Role: Ye aapka "Current Ticket" hai. Har baar jab aap koi data maangte ho (like fetching videos), aap ye token bhejte ho.

Why Short-life? Agar koi hacker ise chura le, toh wo sirf 15 min tak hi tabahi macha payega. Iske baad ye bekar ho jayega.

Payload: Isme user ki basic info (ID, email) hoti hai taaki server aapko pehchan sake.

2. Refresh Token (The Master Key) 🔑
Role: Jab Access Token expire ho jata hai, toh ye token server ke paas jata hai naya Access Token maangne.

Why Long-life? Taaki user ko baar-baar username/password na dalna pade. Ye ek hafton tak valid rehta hai.

Database Link: Isse hum aksar database mein save karte hain taaki agar hacker ka darr ho, toh hum isse "delete" karke user ko logout kar sakein.

3. Storage: HttpOnly Cookie (The Safe Box) 🔒
Hum Refresh Token ko HttpOnly Cookie mein isliye rakhte hain taaki JavaScript usey access na kar sake.

Isse XSS (Cross-Site Scripting) attacks ka khatra khatam ho jata hai. Hacker script chala kar bhi aapka token nahi chura payega.

Summary: Inka Rishta 🤝
JWT ek Format hai. Us format ko use karke hum do tokens banate hain—ek kaam karne ke liye (Access) aur ek system mein bane rehne ke liye (Refresh).

Genie's Tip: Hamesha yaad rakhna, Access Token "What you can do" batata hai, aur Refresh Token "Stay logged in" manage karta hai.


-> some imp points

Jab aap Instagram ya kisi bhi badi app par "Logout from all devices" click karte ho, toh parde ke peeche yahi hota hai:

1. Refresh Token ka "The End" 💀
Server aapke user ID se jude saare Refresh Tokens ko database se delete (ya blacklist) kar deta hai.

2. Access Token ka kya hota hai? ⏱️
Access tokens ko delete nahi kiya ja sakta kyunki wo server ke paas save nahi hote (wo "stateless" hote hain). Lekin, kyunki unki life bahut choti hoti hai (manlo 5-10 mins), wo thodi der mein apne aap expire ho jate hain.

3. Logged Out State 🚫
Jaise hi purana Access Token expire hota hai, app naya mangne ke liye Refresh Token bhejti hai. Par server dekhta hai ki "Bhai, iska toh Refresh Token DB mein hai hi nahi!" aur turant user ko login page par fenk deta hai.

Comparison: Access vs Refresh ExpiryTokenType

Expire
  Hone Par Kya Hota Hai?User ko Pata Chalta Hai?Access TokenApp background mein Refresh Token bhejti hai.Nahi. Sab smooth chalta hai. 🏃‍♂️Refresh TokenApp user ko login screen par bhej deti hai.Haan. User ko firse login karna padta hai. 🛑

  -? Ek Pro Concept: "Refresh Token Rotation" 🔄


Aaj kal ke advance apps mein jab bhi aap Refresh Token use karke naya Access Token mangte ho, server purane Refresh Token ko delete karke ek naya Refresh Token bhi de deta hai. Isse user ka session chalta rehta hai jab tak wo app active use kar raha hai, aur security bhi tight rehti hai.

Genie's Tip: Isi wajah se tumne notice kiya hoga ki Instagram mahino tak login rehta hai (kyunki wo token rotate kar rahe hain), par kuch secure apps har 7 din mein login mangti hain.


# LEC. 11(how to upload file in backend | Multer)


* cloudinary and multer install kr lia

* cloudinary.js naam se ek file bnai in utils usme cloudinary pe file upload krke url lene ka code le lia by providing local file path.

* multer.middleware file bani in middlewares

-> MULTER AND CLOUDINARY
1. Multer Kya Hai? (The Transporter) 🚚
Mongoose ya Express direct file handling nahi samajhte (wo sirf text data samajhte hain). Jab user image upload karta hai, toh data multipart/form-data format mein hota hai.

Kaam: Multer ka kaam hai us file ko parse karna aur tumhare server ke kisi temporary folder (jaise ./public/temp) mein rakh dena.

Kyu Use Karein? Iske bina tum req.file ya req.files ko access nahi kar paoge. Ye file ko "buffer" ya "disk" par store karne mein help karta hai.

2. Cloudinary Kya Hai? (The Warehouse) ☁️
Server pe images save karna buri baat hai (kyunki server crash hua toh data gaya, aur server storage mehenga hota hai).

Kaam: Cloudinary ek Cloud Storage Service hai. Hum Multer se aayi hui file ko Cloudinary pe bhej dete hain.

Result: Cloudinary humein ek URL return karta hai (jaise https://cloudinary.com/user/tushar.jpg). Hum is URL ko apne Database (MongoDB) mein save kar lete hain.

Kyu Use Karein? * Images fast load hoti hain (CDN ki wajah se).

Image resizing aur cropping on-the-fly kar sakte ho.

Tumhara server light-weight rehta hai.

Real-World Workflow (The Master Plan) 🛠️
User ne photo select ki aur "Upload" dabaya.

Multer ne us photo ko pakda aur tumhare server ke temp folder mein save kiya.

Humne ek Utility function likha jo us file ko temp folder se uthakar Cloudinary par upload kar dega.

Cloudinary ne humein ek URL diya.

Humne wo URL MongoDB mein save kiya aur temp folder se file delete kar di.



-> REAL WORLD WORK FLOW

Conceptual level pe Instagram, Facebook, ya WhatsApp sab bilkul aise hi kaam karte hain.

Bas farq itna hai ki Instagram bahut badi company hai, toh wo Cloudinary (jo ki ek third-party service hai) use karne ke bajaye apna khud ka "Storage System" (jaise Facebook ka Haystack ya S3) use karte hain.

Lekin logic 100% wahi hai jo tune samjha. Chal process ko step-by-step dekhte hain:

Insta-style Upload Workflow 📸
Frontend (App): Tu "Post" pe click karta hai. Teri photo ek bundle (Multipart Form Data) ban kar server ki taraf nikal jati hai.

The Middleware (Multer Jaisa): Insta ke servers pe bhi ek "gatekeeper" hota hai (jaise hamara Multer). Wo us file ko pakadta hai aur server ki memory ya ek temporary space mein rakhta hai.

The Storage (Cloudinary Jaisa): Server us photo ko uthakar ek permanent "Cloud Storage" (Jaise AWS S3 ya unka apna server) mein phenk deta hai.

Database (MongoDB Jaisa): Ab main baat—Insta ke database mein photo save nahi hoti, wahan sirf us photo ka URL/Link save hota hai.

Ye do-step process kyu? (Direct kyu nahi?)
Tere dimaag mein aaya hoga ki "Bhai, direct Cloudinary pe kyu nahi bhej dete?"

Security: Hum nahi chahte ki koi bhi random banda hamare Cloudinary account mein kuch bhi bhar de. Server beech mein reh kar check karta hai ki user logged in hai ya nahi.

Processing: Server pe hum photo ko "process" karte hain—jaise uska size kam karna (Compression), filters lagana, ya check karna ki photo mein kuch illegal toh nahi hai. 🛡️

Photo tere phone mein save nahi hoti, wo bas "render" hoti hai.

Chal, iska step-by-step logic samajhte hain:

1. Database ka Link 🔗
Jab kisi ne photo upload ki, toh Cloudinary ne ek URL diya (e.g., https://cloudinary.com/post123.jpg). Ye URL us bande ke Post Schema mein save ho gaya.

2. Feed Fetching (The Query) 🔍
Jab tu apna Insta scroll karta hai, toh tera app server ko ek request bhejta hai: "Bhai, mere dosto ki latest posts dikha."

Server Database mein query maarta hai aur saari posts ka data (Text + Image URL) ek JSON format mein tere phone ko bhej deta hai. Wo JSON kuch aisa dikhta hai:

JSON
{
  "username": "Tushar",
  "caption": "Mausam mast hai! ☁️",
  "postImageUrl": "https://cloudinary.com/post123.jpg"
}
3. Rendering (The Magic) ✨
Tera frontend (React Native ya jo bhi Insta use kar raha hai) is JSON ko padhta hai.

Jahan username hai, wahan "Tushar" likh deta hai.

Jahan postImageUrl hai, wahan ek <img> tag ya Image component banata hai jiska Source (src) wo URL hota hai.

4. Downloading on the Fly 🚀
Jaise hi wo URL tere screen pe aata hai, tera browser/app us URL se photo "fetch" karta hai aur dikha deta hai. Ye itna fast hota hai ki tujhe lagta hai photo app ke andar hi thi.

Pura Flow Summary 📝
Storage: Photo Cloudinary (ya S3) pe hai.

Mapping: Uska link MongoDB mein hai.

Transfer: Link tere phone tak JSON ban ke aaya.

Display: Tere phone ne us link se photo "khich" ke screen pe chipka di.

Fact Check: Agar tu apna internet band karke scroll karega, toh purani cached photos toh dikhengi, par nayi photos ki jagah sirf "khali dabba" dikhega kyunki app URL se photo download nahi kar payega. 💀


