-> 🚀 What is Postman?
Postman is an API platform for developers to design, build, and test their APIs. When you are building a backend, you don't have a frontend (UI) ready yet. Postman acts as your temporary frontend to check if your routes are working.

🛠️ Key Features
Request Testing: You can send GET, POST, PUT, and DELETE requests to your server.

Body Data: It allows you to send complex data like JSON, Text, or even Files (images/videos) to your API.

Headers & Auth: You can easily add API keys or Bearer tokens to test secured routes.

Response View: It shows exactly what your server returns, including the Status Code (e.g., 200 OK, 500 Server Error) and the execution time.

💡 Why not just use the Browser?
A browser's address bar can only perform GET requests. You cannot use it to send a POST request with a password or an image file. Postman gives you the full control you need as a backend engineer.

# LEC. 14(How to use postman for backend)


* req.body se data lelia in user controller

* user route me middleware add krdia

