->  Kaise pehchanein? (The "Rules" Trick)
Tumhe callback ki zaroorat tab hai jab tum ye 3 cheezein karna chahte ho:

1. Jab tumhe har item pe "Personal" nazar rakhni ho
Agar tumhe array ke har element ko ek-ek karke check karna hai (Jaise: "Kya ye empty hai?", "Kya ye 18+ hai?"), toh callback lagega.

Method: some(), every(), find()

Logic: JS loop chalayega, aur har element (x) ko tumhare callback function (rule) me daal kar check karega.

2. Jab tumhe "Badlav" (Transformation) chahiye
Agar tum chahte ho ki array ka har item badal jaye (Jaise: Saare numbers ko double karna).

Method: map()

Logic: Tum callback me bataoge ki kya badalna hai: (num) => num * 2.

3. Jab tumhe "Chhatni" (Filtering) karni ho
Agar tum chahte ho ki puri list me se sirf kaam ke log bachein.

Method: filter()

Logic: Callback me condition doge: (user) => user.isActive === true.

🛠️ Example se samjho:
Dekho dono me farq:

Bina Callback (Simple kaam): array.push("new item") -> JS ko pata hai bas end me dabba jorna hai. No callback needed. ✅

With Callback (Dimaag wala kaam): array.find( (x) => x.id === 1 ) -> JS ko nahi pata tum kaunsi ID dhoond rahe ho, isliye tumhe callback function ke zariye instruction deni padi. 🧠

💡 Pro Tip:
Hamesha check karo: "Kya mujhe array ke har element ke saath kuch specific logic apply karna hai?"

Agar YES -> Callback lagao. (item) => { ... }

Agar NO (Bas delete karna hai, ya add karna hai) -> Direct method use karo.


# LEC. 15(How to use postman for backend)

* if json se data bhejte h to option nhi hota file bhejne ka

- api secret nhi daala tha 
- password field nhi bnaya tha in postman
- next use krne se error aa rha tha because (

  1. Async Style (Jo tu ab use kar raha hai) ✅
Jab tu async function() likhta hai, toh Mongoose ko Promise milta hai.

Mongoose ko next ki zaroorat nahi padti.

Jaise hi tera code await khatam karke function se bahar nikalta hai, Mongoose samajh jata hai ki "Kaam ho gaya, ab save kar do."

Is case mein Mongoose pehle argument mein next bhejta hi nahi hai, isliye jab tu next() call karta hai, toh wo undefined milta hai aur error deta hai.

)



JSON se file bhejne ka default option nahi hota. Hamesha FormData use kar jab bhi image ya file ka chakkar ho.

Normal JSON sirf text-based data (strings, numbers, booleans) carry karne ke liye bana hai. Agar tujhe file (image, pdf, video) bhejni hai, toh tu direct JSON body mein usse nahi daal sakta.

Yahan scene ka overview dekh:

1. JSON vs. FormData 📂
JSON: Jab tu Content-Type: application/json use karta hai, toh tu sirf structured text bhej sakta hai.

FormData: Jab file bhejni hoti hai, tab hum multipart/form-data use karte hain. Ye browser ka wo format hai jo files aur text dono ko mix karke server tak pahunchata hai.

2. Agar JSON se hi bhejni ho? (The Hack) 🛠️
Log kabhi kabhi JSON se file bhejte hain, par wo "raw" file nahi hoti. Wo file ko Base64 string mein convert kar dete hain.

Problem: Isse file ka size ~33% badh jata hai aur server par load zyada aata hai.

Verdict: Bad practice for big files. ❌

3. Sahi Tarika (Standard Flow) 🚀
Backend mein jab tu Multer use karta hai, wo isi multipart/form-data ko handle karne ke liye hota hai.

# LEC. 16(Access Refresh Token, middleware and cookies in backend)


* now we'll make login user in user controller

* gen access and refresh token naam se ek fn bnaya in user controller

* validationbeforesave ka kya scene h .. bcz we use it in gen. tokens in user controller (
  Agar aap {validateBeforeSave: false} nahi lagate, toh ye pange ho sakte the:

  Validation Error: Maan lo aapke UserSchema mein password, email, ya username par required: true laga hai.

  Missing Fields: Is function mein aapne sirf user.refreshToken update kiya hai. Agar Mongoose validation check karta, toh wo bolta: "Bhai, password kahan hai? Email kahan hai?" aur save fail kar deta.

  The Cheat Code: Ye flag lagane se Mongoose ko farq nahi padta ki baki fields mein kya hai, wo chup-chap sirf refreshToken ko update kar deta hai.

    1. Document Method (user.save())
  Jab aap user.save() use karte ho (jaise aapne tokens ke liye kiya), toh aapne pehle database se pura user object nikala hota hai.

  Mongoose ke paas wo pura document memory mein hota hai.

  Aapne sirf user.refreshToken = "nayi_value" kiya.

  Jab aap .save() call karte ho, Mongoose sirf wahi field update karta hai jo badli hai, LEKIN wo validation pure document par chalata hai.

  The Catch: Agar aapne password bheja hi nahi aur schema mein password required hai, toh validation fail ho jayegi. Isliye wahan {validateBeforeSave: false} life-saver hai. ✨

  2. Direct Update Methods (findByIdAndUpdate)
  Agar aap bina user ko fetch kiye direct update karna chahte ho, toh aap sirf wahi field bhejo jo change karni hai.

  JavaScript
  await User.findByIdAndUpdate(userId, {
      $set: { refreshToken: "new_token_here" }
  })
  Isme aapko password ya email se koi lena-dena nahi hai. Baaki fields ko Mongoose touch bhi nahi karega.
  )

  -> imp talk : User (capital U) ek class/model hai, aur user (small u) us class ka ek beta ya instance hai.

  Isko aise samjho:

  1. User (Capital 'U') -> The Blueprint 🏗️
  Ye aapka Model hai. Ye poori collection ki baat karta hai. Iska kaam hai database level pe operations karna, jaise:

  User.find() (Saare users ko dhoondo)

  User.findOne() (Kisi ek ko dhoondo)

  Aap User.isPasswordCorrect() nahi bol sakte, kyunki User ko nahi pata ki kis specific bande ka password check karna hai.

  2. user (Small 'u') -> The Real Person 👤
  Ye wo Document hai jo aapne database se nikal kar ek variable mein save kiya hai.

  Jab aap const user = await User.findOne(...) karte ho, toh database se ek specific bande ka sara data (hash password, email, etc.) is user variable mein aa jata hai.

  Ab is user ke paas apni khud ki identity hai. Isliye aap ispe method chala sakte ho: "Aye user, kya tera password sahi hai?"

  Mongoose Methods ki Vibe Check ⚡
  Mongoose mein do tarah ke functions hote hain:

  Statics: Jo seedha model (User) pe lagte hain. (Pure mohalle ki list nikalne ke liye).

  Methods: Jo ek specific document (user) pe lagte hain. (Ek bande ka secret check karne ke liye).

  Example se clear karo 📝
  Galat: User.isPasswordCorrect(password) ❌ (Bhai, kiska password? Database mein toh 1000 users hain!)

  Sahi: user.isPasswordCorrect(password) ✅ (Is specific user ka password check karo jo humne dhoondha hai.)

  Summary: User (Model) se hum banda dhoondhte hain, aur jab banda (user) mil jata hai, toh uske upar hum apne custom functions (jaise password check karna) chalate hain.


