 (/*
    Frontend: Password change request bheji (Cookies apne aap sath gayi).

    Backend: Check kiya, password badal diya.

    Backend: "Bhai, ye purani cookies delete kar do" (Response bheja with clearCookie).

    Browser: Cookies delete! Ab user ko phir se login karna padega naye password ke saath. Session ekdum fresh! ✨
    Req + Cookie: Jaise req.body mein form ka data aata hai, waise hi req.cookies mein tokens (vibe) aati hain.

    Tokens in Cookies: Cookie bas ek box (storage) hai, asli maal toh uske andar ka Token hi hai.

    Good Practice: Password badalte hi purane session ko "Tata, Bye-bye" bolna security ke liye best hai. Taki agar koi hacker purani cookie lekar baitha ho, toh uska access khatam ho jaye. 🔐✨

    Ab jab tu res.clearCookie() karega, toh user ka current session end ho jayega aur use naye password ke saath fresh login karna padega.
*/)

