* avatarupdate ka controller bnaya h (

  - usi me ek doubtt tha ki user.find by id kyu use kiya direct user.avatar = avatar.url then user.save bhi to krte skte the

  -Bhai, ekdum on point baat pakdi hai tune! Agar tu user.avatar = a.url karega, toh wo data abhi sirf tere server ki memory (RAM) mein hai. Use database ki hard drive tak pahunchane ke liye .save() karna 100% mandatory hai.

  -Main Advice:
  Agar tu Backend Developer ban raha hai, toh ye thumb rule yaad rakh:
  "Jab bhi password ki baat aaye, toh .save() ke paas jao. Baaki sab choti-moti updates ke liye findByIdAndUpdate zindabad!" 🫡


  Bhai, ekdum sahi pakde ho! Agar tum user.save({ validateBeforeSave: false }) karte ho, toh Mongoose saari validations (jaise email format, string length, etc.) ko skip kar deta hai. ⏭️

  Lekin yahan ek bohot bada twist hai jo tujhe samajhna zaroori hai:

  Validation vs Middleware (Hooks)
  Mongoose mein Validation aur Middleware (Pre-save hook) do alag cheezein hain:

  Validation: Ye check karta hai ki data sahi format mein hai ya nahi (e.g., "Email mein @ hai ya nahi?"). { validateBeforeSave: false } likhne se sirf ye rukti hai.

  Middleware (Pre-save Hook): Ye wo function hai jo tune likha tha password hash karne ke liye. Ye nahi rukta! Matlab, chahe tum validation false kar do, tumhara pre("save") wala function phir bhi chalega. Isliye jab tum user.save() karte ho, toh wo password ko hash kar deta hai.

  Agar tum user.save() use karte, toh scene kya hota:
  Piche kya hota?

  Mongoose pre("save") hook pe jata.

  Wahan tumne condition lagayi hai: if(!this.isModified('password')) return;.

  Mongoose check karta: "Bhai, kya password badla hai?"

  Answer milta: "Nahi, sirf avatar badla hai."

  Hook skip ho jata aur data save ho jata. Simple! ✅

  Toh findByIdAndUpdate kyun use kiya?
  Log findByIdAndUpdate isliye use karte hain kyunki:

  Ye Direct Database Query hai.

  Isme poora user object pehle database se nikal kar "memory" mein load nahi karna padta.

  Ye thoda fast hai aur code likhne mein chota lagta hai.

  Summary:
  findByIdAndUpdate = Direct attack on DB (Hooks skip ho jate hain). ⚡

  user.save() = Proper channel (Hooks chalte hain, unless condition roke). 🛡️
)

