# like controller and route

Function 🛠️,Kya Pass Karein? (Input) 📥,Kya Return Hoga? (Output) 📤,Kab Use Karein? 🎯,Example 💻
find(),Filter Object {},Array [...] (Nahi mila toh empty array []),Jab ek se zyada documents nikalne hon.,Video.find({ isPublished: true })
findOne(),Filter Object {},Object {...} (Nahi mila toh null),Jab specific conditions ke sath sirf pehla match chahiye.,"User.findOne({ email: ""a@a.com"" })"
findById(),Sirf _id (String/ObjectId),Object {...} (Nahi mila toh null),Jab directly ID se document uthana ho. Sabse fast! ⚡,User.findById(req.user._id)
create(),Data Object {},Naya Object {...} jo DB me save hua,Naya record/document DB mein add karne ke liye.,"Playlist.create({ name: ""Hits"" })"
findOneAndUpdate(),1. Filter {}2. Update {}3. Options {},Updated Object (agar {new: true} hai varna purana dega),Jab update karte waqt extra filter lagana ho (e.g. owner check).,"Playlist.findOneAndUpdate({_id, owner}, {$set: {name}}, {new: true})"
findByIdAndUpdate(),1. ID2. Update {}3. Options {},Updated Object,Jab bina kisi extra filter ke sidha ID se update marna ho.,"Video.findByIdAndUpdate(id, {$inc: {views: 1}})"
findOneAndDelete(),Filter Object {},Deleted Object ya null,Delete karte waqt extra filter check karna ho (jaise auth).,"Playlist.findOneAndDelete({_id, owner})"
aggregate(),Array of Pipelines [...],Array of Objects [...],Advanced stuff! Jab collections ko join karna ho ya math/stats nikalne hon. 🧠,Video.aggregate([{ $match: {...} }])



💡 Dono Cases ka Difference Dekh:
Case A: Mere Subscribers kaun hain? (Who follows me?)

Logic: channel field mein MERI ID dhundo.

Code: Subscription.find({ channel: myId }).populate("subscriber")

Matlab: Main "Channel" hoon, mujhe dhoondne waale "Subscribers" hain.

Case B: Maine kis-kis ko subscribe kiya hai? (Who do I follow?)

Logic: subscriber field mein MERI ID dhundo.

Code: Subscription.find({ subscriber: myId }).populate("channel")

Matlab: Main "Subscriber" hoon, jinhe main dhoond raha hoon wo "Channels" hain.

1. populate ka Petrol hai ref ⛽
Mongoose ko sapna nahi aayega ki ye ObjectId kis dukaan (model) ki hai. Jab tu schema mein ref: "User" likhta hai, tabhi populate ko pata chalta hai ki use User Collection ki gali mein jaana hai. Agar ref nahi hai, toh populate wahi khada reh jayega.

"Direct Access" ka Jugaad: Aggregation Pipeline 🧠
Agar tere paas schema mein ref Nahi hai, aur fir bhi tujhe doosre model se data chahiye, toh populate() fail ho jayega. Tab aata hai Aggregation Pipeline ka $lookup.

$lookup ko schema ke ref se koi matlab nahi hota. Tu use query ke waqt bata sakta hai:
"Bhai, meri 'subscriber' field ko 'User' model ki '_id' se match kar de aur data le aa."


* params se ID lena tab best hai jab tu Public Profile feature bana raha ho. and req.user._id se ID lena tab best hai jab tu "My Subscriptions" wala private page bana raha ho.

* Jab tu database se koi list/array mangwata hai aur wo khali aata hai (matlab user ne kisi ko subscribe nahi kiya), toh usko 404 Error mat diya kar. Iski jagah 200 OK ke saath ek khali array [] bhej de. Isse frontend walo ko array pe .map() chalane mein error nahi aata aur unka code nahi phat-ta!


// dashboard


ye Aggregation Pipeline ka sabse khatarnak weapon hai: $group. ⚔️

Isko aise samajh: Maan le tere paas 100 videos ka dher (pile) pada hai. $group ka kaam hai un sabko ek bade dabbe mein band karna aur unpe math (calculation) lagana.

🔍 Ek-ek line ka logic breakdown:
1. _id: null (The Grouping Key) 🔑
Aggregation mein humein batana padta hai ki kis basis pe group karna hai (jaise category wise ya date wise).

Lekin Dashboard mein humein poore channel ka Total chahiye, alag-alag tukdon mein nahi.

Jab hum _id: null likhte hain, toh MongoDB samajh jata hai: "Achha, saari matched videos ko ek hi bade group mein daal do."

2. totalVideos: { $sum: 1 } (The Counter) 🔢
Ye ek loop ki tarah kaam karta hai.

Jab MongoDB ko pehli video milti hai, wo +1 karta hai.

Dusri mili, fir +1.

End result: Jitni total videos thi, unka count aa jata hai.

3. totalViews: { $sum: "$views" } (The Adder) 💰
Yahan hum sirf ginn nahi rahe, balki Value add kar rahe hain.

MongoDB har video ke andar jata hai aur uski views waali field ki value uthata hai.

Pehli video (10 views) + Dusri video (50 views) + ...


-> Method 🛠️,Kaise Kaam Karta Hai? 🤔,Performance ⚡
find().length,"Pehle DB se saare documents utha ke backend server pe lata hai, fir JS unhe ginta hai.",Slow 🐌 (Memory aur Network waste hota hai).
countDocuments(),DB engine khud hi apne andar ginti kar leta hai aur sirf ek number bhejta hai.,Fast 🚀 (Ekdum optimized aur lightweight).


* 💡 Isko Ek real-life example se samjh:
Maan le tu ek Library (Video Collection) mein hai. Har Book (Video) pe ek Author ID (localField) likhi hai.
Ab tujhe Author ki poori detail chahiye jo Registration Office (User Collection) mein rakhi hai.

from: "users" (Registration Office mein jao).

localField: "owner" (Mere paas jo Author ID likhi hai use uthao).

foreignField: "_id" (Wahan registration office mein jaake use _id waale column mein dhundho).

as: "authorDetails" (Jo mile use is naam se mere paas le aao).


